Source: NZ Journal of Agriculture
Author:
Vol / Page: 300
Edition:
Quote: The land should be ploughed towards the trees, and a furrow left open between the lines to carry off the surplus water. By so doing, many trees can be saved from "wet feet" now and sour-sap later.
